quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  73,1,O you enwrapped one
  73,2,"Rise to keep vigil at night, except a little"
  73,3,"Half of it, or lessen it a little"
  73,4,Or add to it (a little); and pray and recite the Qur’an calmly and distinctly (with your mind and heart concentrated on it)
  73,5,We will surely charge you with a weighty Word (and with applying it in your daily life and conveying it to others)
  73,6,Rising and praying at night impresses (mind and heart) most strongly and (makes) recitation more certain and upright
  73,7,For by day you have extended preoccupations
  73,8,"And keep in remembrance the Name of your Lord (and mention It in your Prayer), and devote yourself to Him whole-heartedly"
  73,9,"The Lord of the east and the Lord of the west; there is no deity but He, so take Him alone for one to rely on and to entrust your affairs to"
  73,10,"And endure patiently all that they say (against you), and stay aloof from their way (and part from them) in a becoming manner (not as they treat you; rather with forbearance and good advice)"
  73,11,"And leave Me alone to deal with those who enjoy God’s worldly blessings and yet obstinately persist in denying (Our Revelations), and grant them respite for a little while"
  73,12,We have (in store for the likes of them) heavy fetters and a Blazing Flame
  73,13,"And food that chokes, and a painful punishment"
  73,14,"On that Day the earth and the mountains will be violently shaken, and the mountains will be as a heap of slipping sand"
  73,15,"Surely We have sent to you (O people) a Messenger, a witness against you (one who will testify in the Hereafter as to your deeds in response to God’s Message), just as We sent a Messenger to the Pharaoh"
  73,16,"But the Pharaoh rebelled against the Messenger, and so We seized him with a calamitous grasp"
  73,17,"Then how will you, if you persist in unbelief, guard yourselves against a Day which will turn the children gray-headed"
  73,18,The sky will cleft open thereby. His promise (of Resurrection and Judgment) is certainly to be fulfilled
  73,19,"This is a reminder and admonition, and so let him, who wills, take a path to his Lord"